Meet <b>Tracy Jo</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Tracy Jo lives at <a href='/home/?user=tjkitkat'>14422 Glenwood Boulevard</a> in one of the more scenic parts of Golden Valley.  She has only been a citizen since May 02, 2005, but during her brief time here, Tracy Jo has already made a deep impression on the people she's met.<br><br>Despite her short stay in Millsberry, Tracy Jo has already made a large number of friends, who describe her as a friendly and easygoing person.  Due to her sociable nature, Tracy Jo is always more than happy to meet new people.  Don't be too shy to say hello if you see her walking along the streets of <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/main_map.phtml?location=downtown">Downtown Millsberry</a>!  Many a classmate has come to appreciate her compassionate side, as she's always ready to help a friend in need.  Her laid-back temperament makes Tracy Jo easy to approach, and you can easily see why her friends love hanging out with her.<br><br>When they have a chance to get together, Tracy Jo and her friends like to chill in her backyard.  Sometimes, she'll head over to her best friend's house, where they'll have fun hanging out and listening to music.  On weekends, she and her buddies sometimes visit the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/complex/">Downtown Entertainment Complex</a>, where they'll catch the latest movie.<br><br>When she's alone, Tracy Jo likes to either work on her computer or her art.  If you happen to stop in while she's drawing, you'll probably find her covered in black, dark blue, or green chalk, since those are her favorite colors.  When asked, Tracy Jo admits that making chalk drawings is one of her first loves, and she's actually quite good at it!<br><br>Her main interest, however, is music.  While Tracy Jo loves music of all sorts, her favorite genres are country music, modern rock, and classic rock.  She was very excited to hear about the opening of the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/studio/">Millsberry Recording Studio</a>, and was one of the first visitors to stop in for a session.  Don't be surprised if you see Tracy Jo in the studio often this summer, and be sure to check out some of her cool <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/home/?user=tjkitkat">mixes</a> if you have time!<br><br>Along with her many talents, Tracy Jo is also an exemplary citizen, as her gold trophies and good grades from Millsberry Academy prove.  She has also made a great contribution to the effort to keep Peabody Park clean.  Though Tracy Jo hasn't been in Millsberry for very long, her fellow citizens are already grateful that she's here, and she is just as happy to be living here.<br><br>Thanks for being a fine citizen, Tracy Jo, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!</div>
